column1: # Dear prospective user. The following is a sample data file
# that you can submit to the poprep.tzv.fal.de webservice to
# demonstrate, how it can be used.
# The pedigree file needs to have five columns:
# 1. animal ID - treated as character string
# 2. sire ID   - treated as character string
# 3. dam ID    - treated as character string
# 4. birthdate - animal's birthdate (a number of
#                formats are handled (see website)
# 5. sex       - animal's sex: choose your own coding
#                1 - male; 2 - female or m/f
# The columns are separated by the pipe sign:
# Regarding base animals, you have two options:
# 1. list them explictitly as shown here:
# 2. no need to list them at all; then sires and dams
#    that do not have an animal record of their own are
#    considered base animals:
#    No animal record for 4500865 in the pedigree file. We will create an
#    appropriate one for you.
# You can run this pedigree file as is (# comments are ignored) by
# submitting this file to poprep.tzv.fal.de
# Enjoy! EG
